description: Amid heightened tensions following the Pahalgam attack, a BSF constable, PK Sahu, was detained by Pakistan Rangers after inadvertently crossing the international border in Punjab's Ferozepur. Sahu, new to the area, reportedly strayed while monitoring farmers working near the zero-line. BSF is in contact with Rangers, seeking his safe return and requesting further flag meetings.
title: BSF man strays 5 paces into Pakistan, detained by Rangers

description: Mahesh Joshi, a Congress veteran and former Rajasthan minister, was arrested by the ED after a seven-hour interrogation in connection with a multi-crore money laundering case. The arrest, made under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act, follows an investigation triggered by an FIR alleging bribery and irregularities in public health engineering projects during Joshi's tenure as PHED minister.
title: ED arrests ex-Raj Congress minister for money laundering

description: Amid heightened tensions with Pakistan, Indian armed forces are on high alert. Army chief General Upendra Dwivedi is set to visit J&K to review operational readiness along the LoC and counter-terror operations. Simultaneously, the Indian Navy conducted missile tests in the Arabian Sea, mirroring Pakistan's naval exercises, while the Air Force enhances combat skills through 'Aakraman' exercises.
title: IAF carries out 'Aakraman' exercise with Rafales, Navy conducts drill

description: India has intensified its diplomatic response to Pakistan following the Pahalgam attack, briefing foreign envoys, including China, on the cross-border connections of the attackers. The government has revoked visas for Pakistani nationals in India, advising Indian citizens against traveling to Pakistan.
title: India briefs envoys on Pakistan terror links

description: India has formally declared the Indus Waters Treaty in abeyance, citing Pakistan's support for cross-border terrorism and refusal to negotiate as breaches of the agreement. The decision comes after Pakistan warned that any diversion of water allocated to them under the treaty would be considered an act of war.
title: Indus pact in abeyance with immediate effect, unfazed India tells Pak

description: In New Town's Gouranganar, a 29-year-old man, Sanket Chatterjee, was fatally beaten after confronting three men harassing his live-in partner. The incident occurred in the early hours when the woman, having left home after an argument, was accosted by the trio. Despite her pleas and attempts to seek help from neighbors, the assault continued, leading to Sanket's death.
title: Man tries to save girlfriend from harassers, beaten to death

description: Investigators have linked Hashim Musa, a Pakistani attacker, to multiple strikes targeting non-locals in J&K, including the Pahalgam massacre. Security forces are offering a reward for Musa and two other Lashkar terrorists. Evidence suggests Pakistani masterminds guided these attacks, with local aides facilitating the operations. Authorities are actively investigating connections and vulnerabilities to prevent future incidents.
title: Pahalgam attacker part of earlier strikes, had Pakistan handlers
President Murmu to attend Pope funeral tomorrow

description: Following India's suspension of passenger movement, BSF has ceased border gate openings and handshakes at Attari. IG Atul Fulzele confirmed daily flag-lowering ceremonies will continue at Attari, Sadiqi, and Hussainiwala, with heightened security measures including quick response teams and anti-drone technology.
title: BSF keeps Attari gates closed, no customary handshakes now

description: A Delhi court has rejected Tahawwur Rana's request for a phone call with his family. The court cited concerns raised by the National Investigation Agency (NIA) that such communication could jeopardize the ongoing investigation into the 26/11 Mumbai terror attack. The NIA argued that the probe is at a critical stage and Rana might reveal sensitive information.
title: Court rejects Tahawwur Rana plea for phone call with family

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, PM Modi, supported by global leaders like Trump and Putin, vowed retribution, emphasizing international solidarity against terrorism. He expressed the nation's grief and unity, highlighting the diverse backgrounds of the victims and the shared sorrow across the country.
title: 'Everyone who believes in humanity is with us': PM Modi

description: Bihar CM Nitish Kumar publicly accused his JDU colleague and Union Minister Rajiv Ranjan Singh (Lalan Singh) for JDU's short separation from the BJP-led NDA in 2022. Speaking alongside PM Narendra Modi, Nitish reassured that JDU is now firmly aligned with NDA. He also reaffirmed his commitment to fighting against RJD, acknowledging a past mistake of joining hands with them.
title: Nitish Kumar blames colleague Lalan for RJD alliance

description: In a tragic incident, Kaustubh Gunbote and Santosh Jagdale were killed by terrorists in Pahalgam, leaving their families and community in grief. Sangita Gunbote recounted the horrifying moments, including their desperate attempt to appear Muslim to avoid being targeted.
title: Pahalgam attack: 'Removed bindis, chanted Allahu Akbar but our husbands still shot'

description: Prominent Muslim institutions and groups in Uttar Pradesh have vehemently condemned the Pahalgam terror attack, with Darul Uloom Deoband denouncing the act as inhuman and against Islamic teachings. Leaders called for unity and strict action against the perpetrators. Aligarh Muslim University students held a vigil, and residents in Muzaffarnagar protested against terrorism, showcasing a rare display of communal unity.
title: Pahalgam killings against tenets of Islam, says Darul

description: Flights between North India and the West face disruptions as Pakistan closes its airspace, effective Thursday. Indian carriers will take longer routes, potentially adding up to two hours to North America flights and an hour to Europe flights. IndiGo has already cancelled some flights, while Air India and SpiceJet advise passengers to expect extended routes and check flight status.
title: Pakistan closes airspace for Indian carriers

description: Rahul Gandhi has approached the Supreme Court, challenging the summons issued by a UP trial court in the VD Savarkar defamation case. This action follows the Allahabad High Court's rejection of his plea on April 4. Gandhi's petition asserts that the proceedings are frivolous and intended to punish him for exercising his freedoms as an opposition leader.
title: Rahul Gandhi moves SC against court summons over Savarkar remark

description: Fawad Khan's return to Indian cinema with 'Abir Gulaal' faces uncertainty after the Pahalgam terror attack. Public anger has reignited calls to boycott Pakistani talent, potentially leading to the film's ban. The government may withhold release permission amid rising tensions. Theatre owners express reluctance, fearing protests.
title: Release of Fawad Khan's film 'Abir Gulaal' uncertain

description: Fearing for their safety after a threatening video by Hindu Raksha Dal leader Lalit Sharma went viral, six Kashmiri students fled their Dehradun hostel in the early hours of Thursday. Sharma's video warned Kashmiri Muslims to leave Uttarakhand by 10 am or face consequences, prompting the students to rush to the airport.
title: Spooked by threat video, Kashmir students flee Doon

description: Elon Musk announced his reduced role in the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) to focus on Tesla, following a challenging financial quarter for the company. Despite criticism surrounding Musk's cost-cutting efforts, President Trump praised his contributions to federal reform and defended him against perceived unfair treatment.
title: Trump's full remarks on Musk leaving DOGE: At some point, let him ...

description: In Hapur, a 28-year-old man, Shravan Kumar, accused of raping a 10-year-old Dalit girl, died in a Meerut hospital after being thrashed by villagers. The incident occurred on April 17 when Kumar allegedly lured the girl to an empty factory and assaulted her.
title: Man accused of raping Dalit girl, 10, lynched in UP

description: Odisha police have apprehended two active Indian Navy personnel and one former employee in Khurda for allegedly extorting money from Agniveer aspirants. The accused, including Vinay Kumar Ray, Satyam Chahar, and Bhoosan, reportedly demanded between Rs 30,000 and Rs 1.2 lakh from candidates, promising assistance in clearing recruitment stages at INS Chilka.
title: 2 Navy officers held for fleecing Agniveer aspirants

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal etched his name in IPL history during the 2025 match against Royal Challengers Bengaluru, smashing a six off the very first ball. This feat marked his third time achieving this, making him the record holder for most sixes on the first ball of an innings. Earlier, Royal Challengers Bengaluru posted a competitive 205 for five, powered by fluent half-centuries from Virat Kohli (70 off 42) and Devdutt Padikkal (50 off 27).
title: Class act! Yashasvi Jaiswal ahead of Virat Kohli in rare record

description: Karnataka's Deputy CM DK Shivakumar has been actively engaging in spiritual activities, visiting temples and religious leaders, sparking both praise and criticism. While BJP leaders have welcomed his displays of faith, some within his own Congress party worry about the message it sends to their minority support base.
title: DKS' serial visits to temples spark unease in Congress

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) raided Gensol Engineering Ltd offices and detained co-promoter Puneet Singh Jaggi amid financial misconduct allegations. This action, triggered by a SEBI report, accuses the Jaggi brothers of diverting funds obtained from Power Finance Corporation and IREDA Ltd into assets held by promoters and shell companies.
title: ED raids Gensol office, co-founder Puneet Singh Jaggi detained

description: Cricket legend Sunil Gavaskar was seen enjoying a playful moment with Champak, the IPL's new robot dog, at the M. Chinnaswamy Stadium before a match between Royal Challengers Bengaluru and Rajasthan Royals. Champak, named through an online poll referencing a popular TV character, impressed Gavaskar with its ability to jump and run.
title: Gavaskar’s moments with IPL robo-dog Champak go viral - Watch

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru secured a crucial victory against Rajasthan Royals, fueled by Virat Kohli's composed seventy and Josh Hazlewood's game-changing final overs. Kohli's innings anchored Bengaluru's innings, while Hazlewood's exceptional death bowling restricted Rajasthan's chase, ultimately sealing an eleven-run win for the home side. This victory propelled Bengaluru to third place, while Rajasthan's playoff aspirations suffered a setback.
title: Hazlewood delivers RCB’s first Chinnaswamy win in IPL 2025

description: Following a terror attack in Baisaran meadow, Pahalgam, Abdul Waheed Wani, head of the ponywalla association, was among the first responders. He recounted a scene of chaos and grief, with numerous casualties and desperate pleas for help. Despite the challenging circumstances, Wani and other ponywallas played a crucial role in evacuating the injured, while security forces secured the area.
title: 'I'll never be able to forget': First respondent at Pahalgam meadow after massacre

description: Following the tragic Pahalgam massacre, an all-party meeting led by Chief Minister Omar Abdullah strongly condemned the terror attack, emphasizing its assault on Kashmiriyat and Indian values. The resolution supported government measures to bring the perpetrators to justice, honored the pony guide's sacrifice, and praised the Kashmiri people's support for tourists.
title: J&K all-party meet calls Pahalgam massacre 'assault on Kashmiriyat, idea of India'

description: In Kathua, Jammu & Kashmir, journalist Rakesh Sharma was assaulted and hospitalized while covering a BJP protest against the Pahalgam terror attack. The assault occurred after Sharma questioned state security, leading to accusations of “separatist language” by party activist Himanshu Sharma. Other activists, including Ravinder Singh, Ashwani Sharma, and Manjit Singh, joined in the assault.
title: J&K: Kathua journo assaulted while covering BJP protest over terror attack

description: Landslides triggered by incessant rainfall have severely disrupted travel in North Sikkim, specifically along the Lachen–Chungthang and Lachung–Chungthang roads. Authorities have deemed nighttime travel unsafe and suspended the issuance of permits for North Sikkim. All previously issued permits have been cancelled. Relief and repair efforts are underway, but hampered by the continuous downpour.
title: Massive landslides hit north Sikkim; permits for travel suspended amid heavy rain

description: INS Surat successfully tested a surface-to-air missile. The Indian Air Force executed 'Exercise Aakraman' with Rafale jets. These drills occurred after a terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir. Tensions between India and Pakistan have increased. India suspended the Indus treaty. Pakistan responded by suspending the Simla Agreement. Prime Minister Narendra Modi vowed to punish terrorists and their supporters.
title: Navy tests missile; IAF launches huge drill: India gets ready to avenge Pahalgam

description: Sudeep Neupane, 27, was cremated at Triveni Ghat around noon, with hundreds, including local govt officials, gathered for the last rites. Sudeep, his family said, was shot immediately after he identified himself as a Hindu and had no time to explain that he was not from India.
title: Nepal medic killed in Pahalgam didn’t get time to say he was a foreigner

description: Pahalgam sees heavy Army deployment during the Amarnath Yatra, but locals report a reduced presence otherwise. Restrictions are placed on tourist access during the yatra, including the closure of Baisaran meadow. Following Tuesday's terror attack, a large number of troops were present in the meadow, with aerial reconnaissance and combing operations underway.
title: No Army present, say locals; CRPF camp about 5 km from Pahalgam meadow

description: Rajasthan Royals are dominating the IPL 2025 Powerplay with a league-leading 37 sixes, showcasing their aggressive batting strategy. Kolkata Knight Riders, Mumbai Indians, and Punjab Kings follow behind. Chennai Super Kings are surprisingly at the bottom with only five Powerplay sixes. Earlier, Royal Challengers Bengaluru posted a competitive 205 for five, powered by fluent half-centuries from Virat Kohli (70 off 42) and Devdutt Padikkal (50 off 27).
title: No mercy! Rajasthan Royals' brutal Powerplay tactic is shocking everyone

description: During an IPL 2025 match between Royal Challengers Bengaluru and Rajasthan Royals, an umpire's hasty LBW decision created a stir. Initially signaling OUT on Krunal Pandya's appeal against Dhruv Jurel, the umpire quickly reversed his call to NOT OUT after Jurel's review showed a clear inside edge. Earlier, Virat Kohli and Devdutt Padikkal's half-centuries propelled RCB to 205/5 in Bengaluru.
title: On-field umpire overrules third umpire in bizarre IPL blunder

description: Pakistan has put the Simla Agreement on hold, citing India's alleged support for terrorism and disregard for international law. This agreement, signed in 1972, aimed to establish peaceful relations and resolve disputes bilaterally. Experts suggest this move could invalidate the Line of Control and remove restraints on both sides, potentially escalating tensions and impacting India's foreign policy.
title: Pak hold on Simla Agreement signals shift away from peaceful resolution of disputes

description: Bengaluru is set to host the Neeraj Chopra Classic on May 24. This Gold-Label javelin meet will feature top international athletes. Anderson Peters, Thomas Rohler, and Julius Yego are among the stars. Arshad Nadeem will miss the event due to the Asian Athletics Championships. The competition aims to inspire Indian athletes.
title: Pakistan's Nadeem absent as players unveiled for Neeraj Chopra Classic

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26 people, India has taken decisive steps signaling a strong response against Pakistan. Prime Minister Modi vowed to punish the terrorists and their backers, leading to the suspension of visa services for Pakistani nationals and the revocation of existing visas among several other measures.
title: PM Modi's warning rattles Pak as suspense builds over India's next move

description: Virat Kohli achieved a new milestone in T20 cricket. He now holds the record for the most half-centuries while batting first. This happened during the IPL match between Royal Challengers Bengaluru and Rajasthan Royals. Kohli scored 70 runs. RCB reached a total of 205/5. Sandeep Sharma and Jofra Archer took wickets for RR.
title: Record! Kohli leaves Azam behind in another historic milestone

description: The Supreme Court has approved the finalization and notification of the UGC's 2025 Regulations aimed at preventing caste-based discrimination in higher education. While acknowledging concerns raised by student representatives, the court emphasized the regulations' potential benefit to a large number of students. Recommendations from the National Task Force on student suicides will be considered separately.
title: SC approves finalisation of UGC Regulations 2025

description: The Supreme Court has agreed to review a plea challenging the consolidation of four chargesheets related to corruption in appointments for various positions, including assistant engineers and bus drivers, within the Tamil Nadu transport sector. These cases are linked to a cash-for-jobs scam involving minister V Senthil Balaji.
title: SC to hear petition challenging clubbing of Balaji 'scam' cases

description: The Supreme Court questioned the Indian Air Force's denial of family pension to a stepmother who raised her stepson from childhood, enabling him to join the forces. Justices Kant and Singh challenged the IAF's regulations, deeming them inflexible in modern family structures, including surrogacy and adoption.
title: SC: Why no pension for lady who raised stepson?

description: Following the Pahalgam terror attack, an all-party meeting was convened where opposition leaders pledged their support to the government's counter-terrorism efforts. Defence Minister Rajnath Singh briefed attendees on the attack and subsequent government decisions, while security lapses were discussed. Opposition leaders uniformly condemned the attack, emphasising the need for peace in Kashmir and urging the government to take decisive action against terrorism.
title: Security lapses, stricter action: Key points from all-party meet

description: NCR's real estate market is experiencing a significant resurgence, marked by an 81% surge in residential property prices between 2020 and 2025. Greater Noida leads with a 98% price appreciation, followed by Noida and Gurugram. Declining unsold inventory and a shift towards premium housing indicate strong buyer confidence and investment potential, fueled by infrastructure developments and emerging corridors.
title: This NCR locality saw 98% property price surge in just 5 years

description: Sunil Gavaskar passionately condemned the Pahalgam terror attack during a live IPL broadcast, questioning the purpose of the violence and urging for peace. BCCI Secretary Devajit Saikia also issued a strong statement, expressing condolences and solidarity with the victims' families. The BCCI further conveyed its condolences via social media, standing in support of those affected by the tragic event.
title: 'For the last 78 years ... ': Gavaskar's emotional outburst on Live TV

description: Sir Vivian Richards has voiced his support for Babar Azam amidst his current struggles, assuring fans of his imminent return to form. Despite recent poor performances and being dropped from the T20I squad, Richards remains confident in Babar's resilience. Salman Iqbal predicts Babar will surpass even Virat Kohli upon his resurgence, comparing him to legends like Garry Sobers.
title: 'A king is one who ...': Viv Richards makes big Babar Azam comment

description: The Indian Air Force is conducting Exercise Aakraman, a large-scale operational drill in the central sector, featuring Rafale jets and other frontline aircraft. The exercise focuses on advanced mission profiles, including ground attack and electronic warfare, with assets deployed from multiple airbases. This drill comes amid heightened tensions with Pakistan and showcases the IAF's enhanced strategic capabilities with modern weaponry.
title: IAF conducts huge 'Aakraman' exercise amid rising India-Pak tensions

description: In Jammu and Kashmir, terrorists attacked near Pahalgam. Twenty-eight people died in the assault. The Resistance Front claimed responsibility for the attack. The attack happened during US Vice President JD Vance’s India visit. Attackers demanded victims recite Islamic verses. Some survived by reciting the kalma. Pakistan's military posture and mineral ambitions are under scrutiny.
title: Minerals for US, militants for Kashmir: Pak's double game behind J&K attack

description: Former Pakistani cricketer Danish Kaneria criticized Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif for the Pahalgam terror attack, questioning his silence and accusing Pakistan of harboring terrorists. Kaneria defended his loyalty to Pakistan despite being Hindu, highlighting the discrimination faced by Hindus there. The Pahalgam attack — the deadliest since the 2019 Pulwama tragedy — drew widespread condemnation globally. Leaders from around the world, along with prominent voices from the cricketing fraternity and other industries, expressed their condolences to the victims and their families.
title: 'I am a Hindu - a proud one': Ex-Pakistan cricketer on Pahalgam terror attack

description: Rajasthan Royals fans are hopeful as Riyan Parag shares that Sanju Samson is nearing his return from a finger injury. Samson's absence has impacted the team's performance, with the Royals currently struggling in the standings. Parag has stepped up as captain, making strategic changes like bringing in Fazalhaq Farooqi, while eagerly awaiting Samson's comeback to revitalize the team's season.
title: Royals skipper Parag gives massive update on Sanju Samson
Toronto's Pearson Airport shut down after shooting, 1 dead

description: Andrew Flintoff, the former England cricket captain, has opened up about the profound impact of his near-fatal car crash during Top Gear filming in 2022. He candidly admits that he felt it would have been "much easier" if he had died, revealing the depth of his despair following the incident. Flintoff retired from cricket in 2010 at the age of 31, having represented England in 79 Test matches between 1998 and 2009.
title: 'I wish I'd died': England cricket legend's devastating revelation

description: Following the terror attack on tourists in Jammu and Kashmir's Pahalgam, the US government, including President Trump, strongly condemned the violence and expressed condolences to PM Modi. The US House Foreign Affairs Committee corrected the New York Times' use of 'militants,' emphasizing it was a 'terrorist attack.
title: 'This was a TERRORIST ATTACK plain and simple': US Foreign Affairs Committee to NYT

description: US Vice President JD Vance, accompanied by his family, recently visited the Taj Mahal during a four-day trip to India. Vance shared photos on X, with Elon Musk commenting on the monument's beauty. The family's visit included a warm welcome from Uttar Pradesh's Chief Minister and stringent security measures along their route.
title: Elon Musk replies to JD Vance's family photos from Taj Mahal: One of the ...

description: Donald Trump criticized Vladimir Putin following a massive Russian strike on Ukraine that resulted in casualties and significant damage. Trump urged Putin to stop the attacks, citing heavy troop losses and advocating for a peace deal. The strikes targeted Ukraine's aviation, aerospace, and defense industries, prompting President Zelenskyy to condemn Russia's actions and appeal for international awareness and accountability.
title: 'Vladimir, STOP!': In rare criticism, Donald Trump urges Putin to end war

description: Assam Police arrested AIUDF MLA Aminul Islam for allegedly making derogatory remarks about the Pahalgam terror attack during a public gathering. His statement, deemed misleading and instigating, went viral, prompting charges under the Bharatiya Nyay Samhita. Chief Minister Sarma vowed strong action against anyone defending the attack.
title: Assam Police arrests AIUDF MLA Aminul Islam over remarks on Pahalgam attack

description: ​Princess Isabella of Denmark is the second child and the elder daughter of King Frederik X and Queen Mary. She is the fourth grandchild and oldest granddaughter of Queen Margrethe II and Prince Henrik. She was the first girl born into the Danish royal family since the birth of her great aunt, Queen Anne-Marie of Greece, in 1946.
title: 'This is bizarre': Princess Isabella breaks royal protocol for 18th bday photo

description: India may soon be the first nation to strike a bilateral trade deal with the US under President Trump's reciprocal tariff policy, according to US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent. Negotiations are reportedly near a breakthrough, facilitated by India's relatively low tariffs and minimal trade barriers.
title: ‘Very close’: India may be first to sign trade pact, says US treasury secy

description: Rohit Sharma's brilliant 70 and a 53-run partnership with Suryakumar Yadav propelled Mumbai Indians to a dominant seven-wicket victory over Sunrisers Hyderabad. Mumbai chased down the 144-run target with ease, securing their fourth consecutive win. Earlier, Heinrich Klaasen's 71 helped SRH recover to 143/8, but it wasn't enough to stop Mumbai's momentum.
title: Shami calls Hardik Pandya 'bhai' and asks for his autograph

description: A new report from the American Lung Association reveals that over 25 million more Americans are breathing polluted air, increasing health risks. Climate events like wildfires and heatwaves are worsening air quality, especially in the West Coast and areas affected by Canadian wildfires.
title: Air pollution in US: These 10 major cities are most affected
BSF jawan detained by Pak Rangers after he accidentally crosses border
Rattled by India, Pak suspends Simla peace treaty: What is it?

description: Following a terrorist attack in Pahalgam, Prime Minister Modi pledged decisive action against those responsible, vowing to "identify, track, and punish" the perpetrators. Pakistan responded sharply, warning that any threat to its sovereignty would be met with "firm reciprocal measures." Islamabad condemned India's suspension of the Indus Waters Treaty as an "Act of War," and took retaliatory measures, including airspace closure, trade suspension, and the expulsion of Indian military advisors.
title: 'Act of war': Pak reacts to India's big move after J&K attack

description: India has suspended all visas for Pakistani citizens. They must leave the country by April 27. Medical visas are valid until April 29. This decision follows the Pahalgam terror attack. PM Narendra Modi vowed to punish those responsible. Indians are advised against traveling to Pakistan. Those in Pakistan should return home soon.
title: All Pakistan nationals ordered to leave India within 72 hrs

description: Amidst outrage over the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 28 tourists, a video showing a man carrying a cake to the Pakistan High Commission has sparked controversy. Simultaneously, protests erupted in Delhi, with demonstrators demanding decisive action against Pakistan.
title: Cake delivery for Pak High Commission going viral after Pahalgam attack

description: Shital Kalathiya, wife of slain Surat banker Shailesh Kalathiya, has demanded justice following the Pahalgam terror attack. At her husband's funeral, attended by ministers and a large crowd, she criticized the security arrangements in Jammu and Kashmir. She alleged security forces failed to protect citizens and questioned why VIPs receive preferential treatment while her husband lacked essential security.
title: 'They kept on laughing till my husband died': Wife laments inadequate security

description: Microsoft is implementing a new performance strategy, offering underperforming employees a severance package of 16 weeks' pay to voluntarily leave instead of entering a Performance Improvement Plan (PIP). Employees have five days to decide, and those choosing the PIP forfeit the payout.
title: Microsoft HR head gives employees 5 days 'deadline' to ... or leave the company

description: In Pahalgam, Kashmir, a terror attack killed Navy Lieutenant Vinay Narwal. He was honeymooning with his wife, Himanshi, when gunmen attacked. Irshad Ahmad, a local, helped them after the shooting. Narwal, recently married, died at the scene. His family in Karnal mourns the loss. The Navy and community remember him as a dedicated officer. Authorities are investigating the attack.
title: 'Lied to his wife that he was alive': Operator who rushed navy officer to ambulance
